1).npm run test 
                Runs command from package.json
                Usually runs all test files
                Uses project config (playwright.config.js)
                Standard command for teams/projects


2).npx playwright test file_name
                  Runs Playwright directly
                  Executes only one specific test file
                  Faster for development
                  No need to depend on package.json scripts
3).npx playwright test file_name  --debug 
                  Runs test in debug mode
                  Opens browser + Playwright Inspector
                  Allows step-by-step execution
                  Helps find errors easily
4).npx playwright test v10.spec.js --headed
                  Single file run headless


5).npm install -D allure-playwright
            npx allure generate ./allure-results
            Or 
            npx allure open ./allure-report





  